---
// Two-panel schematic contrasting single-shot LLM critique with the synthesiser-and-auditor pattern.
// Pure SVG, no client-side JS.
---

<figure class="schem">
  <svg viewBox="0 0 760 380" preserveAspectRatio="xMidYMid meet" aria-label="Comparison of single-shot LLM critique and synthesiser-and-auditor architecture">
    <defs>
      <marker id="schem-arrow" viewBox="0 0 10 10" refX="9" refY="5" markerWidth="6" markerHeight="6" orient="auto">
        <path d="M0,0 L10,5 L0,10 z" class="arrowhead" />
      </marker>
      <marker id="schem-arrow-bad" viewBox="0 0 10 10" refX="9" refY="5" markerWidth="6" markerHeight="6" orient="auto">
        <path d="M0,0 L10,5 L0,10 z" class="arrowhead-bad" />
      </marker>
      <marker id="schem-arrow-feedback" viewBox="0 0 10 10" refX="9" refY="5" markerWidth="6" markerHeight="6" orient="auto">
        <path d="M0,0 L10,5 L0,10 z" class="arrowhead-feedback" />
      </marker>
    </defs>

    <!-- Panel A: single-shot -->
    <g class="panel panel-bad">
      <text x="180" y="24" text-anchor="middle" class="panel-title">Single-shot critique</text>

      <rect x="120" y="48" width="120" height="40" rx="4" class="node node-input" />
      <text x="180" y="72" text-anchor="middle" class="node-label">Document</text>

      <rect x="120" y="128" width="120" height="40" rx="4" class="node node-llm" />
      <text x="180" y="148" text-anchor="middle" class="node-label">LLM</text>
      <text x="180" y="162" text-anchor="middle" class="node-sublabel">no source access</text>

      <rect x="105" y="208" width="150" height="48" rx="4" class="node node-bad-out" />
      <text x="180" y="228" text-anchor="middle" class="node-label">Critique</text>
      <text x="180" y="244" text-anchor="middle" class="node-sublabel">fluent · confident · ungrounded</text>

      <rect x="120" y="296" width="120" height="40" rx="4" class="node node-human" />
      <text x="180" y="320" text-anchor="middle" class="node-label">Lawyer</text>

      <line x1="180" y1="88"  x2="180" y2="124" class="edge" marker-end="url(#schem-arrow)" />
      <line x1="180" y1="168" x2="180" y2="204" class="edge" marker-end="url(#schem-arrow)" />
      <line x1="180" y1="256" x2="180" y2="292" class="edge edge-bad" marker-end="url(#schem-arrow-bad)" />

      <text x="290" y="278" text-anchor="start" class="annot annot-bad">structure mistaken</text>
      <text x="290" y="292" text-anchor="start" class="annot annot-bad">for substance</text>
    </g>

    <!-- Divider -->
    <line x1="380" y1="40" x2="380" y2="356" class="divider" />

    <!-- Panel B: synthesiser-and-auditor -->
    <g class="panel panel-good">
      <text x="570" y="24" text-anchor="middle" class="panel-title">Synthesiser &amp; auditor loop</text>

      <rect x="510" y="48" width="120" height="40" rx="4" class="node node-input" />
      <text x="570" y="72" text-anchor="middle" class="node-label">Document</text>

      <rect x="510" y="128" width="120" height="40" rx="4" class="node node-llm" />
      <text x="570" y="148" text-anchor="middle" class="node-label">Synthesiser</text>
      <text x="570" y="162" text-anchor="middle" class="node-sublabel">drafts · proposes</text>

      <!-- Auditor side branch -->
      <rect x="660" y="128" width="90" height="40" rx="4" class="node node-source" />
      <text x="705" y="153" text-anchor="middle" class="node-label">Sources</text>

      <rect x="510" y="208" width="120" height="40" rx="4" class="node node-auditor" />
      <text x="570" y="228" text-anchor="middle" class="node-label">Auditor</text>
      <text x="570" y="242" text-anchor="middle" class="node-sublabel">checks atomic claims</text>

      <rect x="490" y="270" width="160" height="36" rx="4" class="node node-worklist" />
      <text x="570" y="293" text-anchor="middle" class="node-label-sm">ranked worklist + sources</text>

      <rect x="510" y="328" width="120" height="40" rx="4" class="node node-human node-human-good" />
      <text x="570" y="346" text-anchor="middle" class="node-label">Lawyer</text>
      <text x="570" y="358" text-anchor="middle" class="node-sublabel">prioritises · debugs</text>

      <!-- Forward edges -->
      <line x1="570" y1="88"  x2="570" y2="124" class="edge" marker-end="url(#schem-arrow)" />
      <text x="585" y="110" class="edge-label">draft</text>

      <line x1="570" y1="168" x2="570" y2="204" class="edge" marker-end="url(#schem-arrow)" />
      <text x="585" y="190" class="edge-label">atomic claims</text>

      <line x1="660" y1="148" x2="634" y2="148" class="edge" marker-end="url(#schem-arrow)" />
      <line x1="660" y1="148" x2="660" y2="200" class="edge" />
      <line x1="660" y1="200" x2="634" y2="218" class="edge" marker-end="url(#schem-arrow)" />
      <text x="668" y="186" class="edge-label">evidence</text>

      <line x1="570" y1="248" x2="570" y2="266" class="edge" marker-end="url(#schem-arrow)" />
      <line x1="570" y1="306" x2="570" y2="324" class="edge" marker-end="url(#schem-arrow)" />

      <!-- Feedback loop: lawyer's prioritised output back to auditor -->
      <path d="M 510 348 C 420 348, 420 228, 506 228" class="edge edge-feedback" marker-end="url(#schem-arrow-feedback)" />
      <text x="416" y="284" text-anchor="middle" class="edge-label edge-label-feedback">prioritised</text>
      <text x="416" y="296" text-anchor="middle" class="edge-label edge-label-feedback">follow-up</text>

      <!-- Information asymmetry annotation -->
      <path d="M 470 152 Q 458 188 470 222" class="asym-bracket" />
      <text x="455" y="190" text-anchor="end" class="annot">information</text>
      <text x="455" y="202" text-anchor="end" class="annot">asymmetry</text>
    </g>
  </svg>
  <figcaption>
    The single-shot pattern (left) collapses generation, criticism and verification into one un-grounded pass; the lawyer is downstream of an opaque output. The synthesiser-and-auditor pattern (right) is an iterative loop: roles are separated, the auditor has independent source access, the lawyer becomes the prioritisation gate, and the lawyer's prioritised follow-up feeds back to the auditor for the next round. The system never autonomously concludes; the loop terminates when the lawyer says it does.
  </figcaption>
</figure>

<style>
  .schem {
    width: 100%;
    max-width: 760px;
    margin: 1.5rem auto;
    color: var(--post-text, #353535);
    font-family: ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif;
  }
  .schem svg { width: 100%; height: auto; display: block; }

  .schem .panel-title {
    fill: var(--post-heading, #1a1a1a);
    font-size: 14px;
    font-weight: 600;
  }
  .schem .divider {
    stroke: var(--post-separator, #bbb);
    stroke-dasharray: 3 3;
    stroke-opacity: 0.6;
  }

  .schem .node {
    fill: var(--post-bg, #fff);
    stroke: var(--post-text, #353535);
    stroke-width: 1.2;
  }
  .schem .node-input { stroke: var(--post-caption, #737373); }
  .schem .node-llm { stroke: var(--post-text, #353535); }
  .schem .node-source { stroke: var(--post-caption, #737373); stroke-dasharray: 4 2; }
  .schem .node-auditor { stroke: var(--post-link, #2563eb); }
  .schem .node-worklist {
    fill: var(--post-bg, #fff);
    stroke: var(--post-link, #2563eb);
    stroke-dasharray: 4 2;
  }
  .schem .node-human { stroke: var(--post-text, #353535); }
  .schem .node-human-good { stroke: var(--post-link, #2563eb); stroke-width: 1.5; }
  .schem .node-bad-out {
    fill: var(--post-bg, #fff);
    stroke: #dc2626;
    stroke-width: 1.2;
  }

  .schem .node-label {
    fill: var(--post-heading, #1a1a1a);
    font-size: 12px;
    font-weight: 500;
  }
  .schem .node-label-sm {
    fill: var(--post-heading, #1a1a1a);
    font-size: 11px;
    font-weight: 500;
  }
  .schem .node-sublabel {
    fill: var(--post-caption, #737373);
    font-size: 10px;
  }

  .schem .edge {
    stroke: var(--post-text, #353535);
    stroke-width: 1.2;
    fill: none;
  }
  .schem .edge-bad { stroke: #dc2626; }
  .schem .edge-feedback {
    stroke: var(--post-link, #2563eb);
    stroke-width: 1.4;
    stroke-dasharray: 5 3;
    fill: none;
  }
  .schem .arrowhead { fill: var(--post-text, #353535); }
  .schem .arrowhead-bad { fill: #dc2626; }
  .schem .arrowhead-feedback { fill: var(--post-link, #2563eb); }
  .schem .edge-label-feedback {
    fill: var(--post-link, #2563eb);
    font-style: italic;
  }

  .schem .edge-label {
    fill: var(--post-caption, #737373);
    font-size: 10px;
  }
  .schem .annot {
    fill: var(--post-caption, #737373);
    font-size: 10px;
    font-style: italic;
  }
  .schem .annot-bad {
    fill: #dc2626;
    font-size: 10px;
    font-style: italic;
  }
  .schem .asym-bracket {
    stroke: var(--post-caption, #737373);
    stroke-width: 1;
    fill: none;
    stroke-dasharray: 2 2;
  }

  .schem figcaption {
    margin-top: 0.5rem;
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: var(--post-caption, #737373);
    text-align: center;
    line-height: 1.4;
  }
</style>
